HEADWORD: Leucophane
<hw>Leu"co*phane</hw> <pr>(l⟦umac⟧"k⟦osl⟧*f⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>leykofanh`s</grk> appearing bright or white;
<grk>leyko`s</grk> white + <grk>fai`nein</grk> to show: cf. G.
<ets>leukophan</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a
greenish yellow color; it is a silicate of glucina, lime, and soda with
fluorine. Called also <altname>leucophanite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

